title: Infant mortality rate in the Netherlands 2008 to 2018
yAxis: Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children, containing a total of 11 data points.
Overall Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children has decreased over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2014 and 2015.
The highest Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children, of value 3.8 was reached at Year 2008,  2009,  2010, and 2013
Minimum Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children about 3.3 was reached at Year 2015
min_summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children. In total the number of data points it has is 11.
Overall Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children has decreased over the Year.

Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children is roughly constant from 2008 to 2010, slightly decreasing from 2010 to 2011, slightly increasing from 2011 to 2012, gradually decreasing from 2012 to 2015, slightly increasing from 2015 to 2016, and finally roughly decreasing from 2016 to 2018.
